article.headline: Air Force secures 69-61 win against Stony Brook
article.description: — Wesley Celichowski's 22 points helped Air Force defeat Stony Brook 69-61 on Saturday.
article.linkText: Air Force secures 69-61 win against Stony Brook
article.story: FRISCO, Texas -- — Wesley Celichowski's 22 points helped Air Force defeat Stony Brook 69-61 on Saturday. Celichowski shot 6 of 10 from the field, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 8 for 8 from the line for the Falcons (3-7). Ethan Taylor scored 17 points while going 6 of 11 (3 for 6 from 3-point range) and added eight rebounds, six assists, and three steals. Caleb Walker shot 6 of 6 from the field and 2 of 4 from the free-throw line to finish with 14 points. The Seawolves (2-7) were led by CJ Luster II, who recorded 27 points. Stony Brook also got 13 points from Collin O'Connor. Andre Snoddy finished with 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
